<br>
Why?  Because on the off chance my pet does run off, I can know if he's engaged any monsters with his 'taunting attackers' message.  <br>
<br>
This hasn't happened in fear yet, but if it was to, I'd run away from the camp, warn everyone that my pet ran into something, /q and hope I'm not dead when I come back.<br>
<br>
It did happen in Hate once, and I had enough time to move away from the camp and log out.  I was lucky to have time, I expected to die.<br>
<br>
Of course, if a pet does run off, you need to kill it with an invis asap..  The insta-invis to animals of earthen boots is useful for this..  except if you do see a 'taunting attacker' message -- that means that when your pet dies, the mob(s) are coming for you next.  Read above for instructions. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
ALWAYS log out and come back after a pet gets loose, even if nothing bad comes of it..  a mob might be wandering around spreading you around various hate lists for a while before they all rush to train you -- and the camp -- unexpectedly.<br>
<br>
You can't be lazy in fear or hate.  There will be lots of mez'd mobs, and you have to make sure if your pet is on the right one.  Don't be afraid to kill your pet so an enc can mez if you can't get it off a mob.<br>
<br>
Have kill switches for your pet hotkeyed.  Definitely /pet get lost, and you should have an invis item in case he's out of range.<br>
<br>
Like someone said above, always listen to your raid leaders.  Do not debate pet policies during a raid.  It's their call.  It's frustrating not to be able to use them, but that's life.<br>
<br>
A golden newbie rule for plane raids is, you cannot -- under any circumstance -- train the camp.  If you're on your way to the camp and attacked, stop and die.  You'll be rez'd.  You need to prepare for death.<br>
<br>
You'll get moments in raids where it looks like there's going to be a mass death.  The raid leader will call for clerics to camp.  In hate, only clerics go on the wall to camp.  Everyone else waits until they're gone before camping.  The idea is that you buy the clerics as much time to camp as possible, they need to rez everyone.  If no clerics camp during a mass death, life gets very hard..  I usually summon a pet for this, my earth pet can distract a mob a lot longer than I can..<br>
<br>
In Hate, __do not__ fight on the wall at the sw camp.  During downtime, you wait sit around 90% of the way up the wall.  The raid leader will have macros to tell everyone to come down and assist him when they have a mob ready.  Even if you're oom, come down to the floor to med, do not stay on the wall during combat.  You need to keep the mobs off the wall, and away from the cleric in the sw corner -- life's a bitch otherwise.<br>
<br>
During Naggy raids, use your fire pet against Naggy, it has the best resistances to fire. Against Vox, use water.  Your fire pet peobably won't be killed by naggy.  I haven't done trakanon yet, but he has poison attacks, so you'll want your water pet -- get yourself a gsd too. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I hope these scattered, unorganized tips help..  I'm sleepy. <br>
<br>
